-- Adversarial soundness probes.
-- Each probe is classified by running it twice: once with --check, once for real.
--
--   TYPECHECK_REJECT  --check exits nonzero (the type system caught it)
--   PANIC             --check passes, but running exits nonzero
--   CLEAN_RUN         --check passes and running exits zero
--
-- The point is not that a probe "passes" — it is that its classification never
-- silently downgrades. A TYPECHECK_REJECT that becomes a PANIC means the type
-- system stopped catching something. A PANIC that becomes a CLEAN_RUN is worse:
-- it means a program that should have crashed now returns a wrong answer.
--
-- FORMAT: -- EXPECT: <classification>
-- <code, one or more lines, until the next EXPECT>

-- ===== linear discipline: boxes must be consumed exactly once =====

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- box is linear: not copyable
42 box dup

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- box is linear: drop is for stackables
42 box drop

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- box is linear: must be consumed, not abandoned
42 box

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- consumed twice
42 box dup free free

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- free rejects dicts at type time
dict free

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- the sanctioned lifecycle
42 box free

-- ===== protocol constraints =====

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- symbols are Eq-only, never Ord
'a 'b lt

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- sort needs Ord; symbols are not
['a 'b] sort

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- mod is Integral: floats are not
1.0 2.0 mod

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- no implicit int/float coercion
1 2.0 plus

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- symbols do support Eq
'a 'a eq drop

-- ===== either / tagged discipline =====

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- default's fallback must match the 'ok payload type: () is a tuple, the
-- list's elements are ints
[1 2 3] pop () default

-- EXPECT: TYPECHECK_REJECT
-- ...and a string fallback cannot stand in for an int payload either
[1 2 3] pop "str" default len drop

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- the (()) idiom is fine when the payload really is a tuple
[(1 2) (3 4)] pop (()) default drop

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- a fallback of the right type is fine
[1 2 3] pop -1 default drop

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- the empty-list path takes the fallback
[] pop -1 default drop

-- ===== runtime panics: programmer errors that types cannot see =====

-- EXPECT: PANIC
-- division by zero
1 0 div drop

-- EXPECT: PANIC
-- modulo by zero
1 0 mod drop

-- EXPECT: PANIC
-- must on a 'no value
none must drop

-- EXPECT: PANIC
-- index out of bounds, unwrapped
[1 2 3] 99 get must drop

-- ===== fallible ops must not panic; they return tagged =====

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- out-of-bounds get is 'no, not a crash
[1 2 3] 99 get 0 default drop

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- take-n clamps rather than panicking
[1 2 3] 99 take-n drop

-- EXPECT: CLEAN_RUN
-- drop-n clamps rather than panicking
[1 2 3] 99 drop-n drop
